Female (
Fig. 17
). Length 3.7–4.4 mm . As in male except integument lighter, reddish brown. Rostrum considerably less densely squamose, distal part more broadened to apex, finely punctured, with antennal insertion after middle of rostrum length. Recumbent scales on pronotum sides yellowish, scaling of elytra markedly reduced, mostly to transverse bands and apical patches. Elytra between bands only with blackish, subrecumbent sharp setalike scales. Spermatheca: Fig. 10 .
